Charles Okah has been sentenced to life imprisonment for his role in the 2010 Independence Day bombing in Abuja. Premiumtimesng.com reports that Â Charles, the younger brother of Henry Okah, was sentenced by the Federal High Court in Abuja on Wednesday evening. He was sentenced alongside Obi Nwabueze, his co-accused for the crime. The elder Okah had been sentenced for a similar crime in South Africa, where he was based. A dozen people were killed in the bombing at Eagle Square, Abuja during the Goodluck Jonathan administration.